OL,3,CFears care home could close after 40
OL,4,Cyears due to NHS 'bed blocking'
OL,6,FA care home in Hove, and many others,
OL,7,Fmay have to close because they don't
OL,8,Fhave enough residents - despite the
OL,9,Fneed for care being greater than ever.
OL,11,FChurchley Rest Home on New Church Road
OL,12,Fhas been running for almost 40 years.
OL,14,FBut staff say bed blocking in the NHS
OL,15,Fand a shortage of social workers able
OL,16,Fto make referrals has left them
OL,17,Fstruggling to stay open.
OL,19,FResident Elspeth Parsons-Glover, 95,
OL,20,Fsaid she would be devastated.
